    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "t_start": 0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Physics calls it a stationary state. Stationary means nothing changes. But write the wavefunction down and it never stops spinning.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reveal"
      },
      "card": {
        "dek": "The phasor that spins but never changes anything",
        "eyebrow": "QUANTUM MECHANICS"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.37,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "t_start": 9,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "An energy eigenstate rotates in the complex plane at rate E over h-bar. Its probability stays flat. How can something rotate and change nothing?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reveal"
      },
      "card": {
        "dek": "e^{-iEt/hbar} rotates without stop. |psi|^2 never moves. Why?",
        "eyebrow": "THE QUESTION"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.46,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 19,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The wavefunction psi lives in the complex plane \u2014 a two-component thing with a real part and an imaginary part. When time passes, the state rotates.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.93,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 30,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The time factor is e to the minus-i-E-t-over-hbar. That is a unit arrow. Its length is exactly one. Always.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.36,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 40,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Probability is not psi \u2014 it is psi-star times psi, the modulus squared. When you multiply a unit arrow by its conjugate, the phases cancel exactly.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "transform"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.89,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 52,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Watch: psi rotates left, psi-star rotates right by the same amount. Their product stays pinned at the same real number, no matter the angle.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.33,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 63,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The spatial part psi-of-x carries all the shape information. The time factor is a pure phase \u2014 it dresses the shape but contributes zero to any probability.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.38,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-phasor-stationary/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-phasor-stationary/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "t_start": 74,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Stationary does not mean frozen in the complex plane. It means every observable \u2014 every number you can measure \u2014 stays constant in time.",
      "shot": {
